<TEXT>
attorney general edwin meese iii is the 
apparent target of anonymous graffiti artists who have left 
inscriptions such as sleazy and resign on the walls of the 
main justice department building 
the graffiti began appearing at about the time two top aides to 
meese resigned march 29 due to concern about problems associated 
with the criminal investigation of meese 
the word sleazy last week was scrawled in black 4inchhigh 
letters on a secondfloor staircase in the middle of the building 
the stairwell is far from meeses fifthfloor office but is heavily 
traveled 
employees first noticed the graffiti there friday said a 
justice department lawyer who spoke on condition of anonymity 
the basement and firstfloor levels of the staircase are heavily 
traveled because they lead to the cafeteria 
in another instance the word resign was scribbled on a wall 
near meeses office but it was cleaned off quickly said department 
sources speaking on condition of anonymity 
such graffiti started appearing around the same time that deputy 
attorney general arnold burns and criminal division chief william 
weld submitted their protest resignations march 29 the course said 
burns and weld quit out of concern that meeses continued tenure 
as attorney general was hurting the justice departments operation 
morale and public image sources said 
meese was in rome on monday for a meeting of police executives 
independent counsel james mckay last may 11 launched an 
investigation of meeses activities including his involvement with 
the scandalplagued wedtech corp a 1 billion iraqi oil pipeline 
the probe also has examined his holdings of regional bell telephone 
stock and his wifes 40000ayear job the money for ursula 
meeses job comes from a washington family whose real estate 
company leases office space to the justice department 
