<TEXT>
a communist party member harshly criticized his 
comrades in a letter to pravda saying their careerist ambitions 
and conformity made the party into a mere instrument of josef 
stalin and his successors 
the letter from a government official v selivanov to the 
party daily differed markedly from the usual criticism now seen of 
the soviet past which blames former party leaders themselves for 
excesses or departures from marxistleninist orthodoxy 
selivanov deputy chief of administration at the ministry of the 
aviation industry criticized the 19million member party itself 
and its role in his countrys political life since the death of 
vladimir i lenin in 1924 
selivanov a party member since 1972 wrote the party is the 
mind honor and conscience of our epoch those words of vi 
lenin unfortunately cannot be applied to all members of our party 
at the current time 
his letter frontpaged in pravdas monday editions appeared the 
day after may day the workers holiday and its prominent place was 
clearly designed to give its contents maximum exposure 
soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev has told party members to 
back his ambitious program for perestroika or social and 
economic restructuring or get out of the way for those who do he 
is expected to use a party conference on june 28 to set his stamp 
even more firmly on the party which holds the monopoly on soviet 
political power 
the main question of perestroika is the democratization of 
society and this is not feasible without democratization of the 
party selivanov wrote in this letter to that end he called for 
reviewing each communists past performance to see whether 
membership should be extended or revoked 
the nations criminal code now being rewritten should be 
modified so communists who commit crimes get a more severe sentence 
than nonparty members he said party leaders up to the level of 
regional chief should be elected for a set term by secret ballot 
he said top local party officials are now appointed by moscow and 
the appointment ratified by a ritual vote 
gorbachev himself floated the idea of a more democratic 
selection process for local party officials at the party central 
committees meeting in january 1987 the idea was not repeated in 
the central committees report indicating a defeat for gorbachev 
but it has resurfaced in speeches by soviet officials 
analyzing the often troubled role of the party during 70 years 
of soviet history selivanov wrote that during the internecine 
ideological battles of the late 1920s and 1930s the party 
leadership pursued unity at any price 
the result he said was the spread of the opinion that the 
gensec party general secretary is always right that his speeches 
are the truth down to the last detail it is only necessary to 
correctly quote the leader 
during their tenures as party leader stalin nikita s 
khrushchev and leonid i brezhnev all had no intention of modifying 
the party structures that concentrated so much power in their 
hands selivanov wrote 
for many communists and their families the careers awards 
benefits and contacts with influential people they could obtain 
from their party membership became the chief goals in their lives 
he said 
in the 1970s when brezhnev was in power selivanov said some 
people told him that having intelligence and a conscience was 
incompatible with being a member of the communist party 
</TEXT>
