here at a glance are the methods for picking 
delegates from ohio to attend the 1988 democratic and republican 
national conventions this summer 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
method primary 
date tuesday may 3 
pledged delegates159 super delegates 15 total 174 
delegates allocated tuesday may 3 
selection of delegatestuesday may 3 and friday june 10 
 
ohio democrats pick pledged national convention delegates 
through a presidential preference primary on may 3 
the states 104 pledged delegates from congressional districts 
will be elected directly from the primary ballot the presidential 
candidate receiving the most votes in a congressional district will 
receive one bonus delegate from that district and the remaining 
delegates will be allocated among presidential candidates in 
proportion to the results of the primary 
ohios remaining 55 pledged national convention delegates will 
be chosen by the partys executive committee on june 10 and will be 
allocated among presidential candidates in proportion to the 
results of the primary 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
method primary 
date tuesday may 3 
delegates 88 
delegates allocated tuesday may 3 
selection of delegates tuesday may 3 
 
ohio republicans elect their national convention delegates 
directly from the may 3 primary ballot 
ohio is a winnertakeall state so the candidate getting the 
most votes in each congressional district will get all three of the 
convention delegates from those districts 
the remaining 25 delegates at large are awarded to the candidate 
receiving the most votes statewide 
