were traced mostly to pornographic numbers 
between early november and late december 93 calls were made 
mostly during the day from various agency telephones 
the number of calls showed surprisingly little abuse of 
state telephone lines administrative services secretary george e 
hale said monday 
the survey turned up 7533 in direct tolls for calls to special 
service lines although the report did not detail costs charged for 
calls on the states widearea bulkcalling service 
i reached the conclusion that from a financial standpoint 
its not a significant problem hale said although it does 
raise questions about what the individual employees involved have 
to do with their time 
