this hope must not be deceived or then it will not be easy to 
restore faith to the people to elevate them to great tasks 
yeltsin told the daily stroitelnaya gazeta construction newspaper 
in an interview 
yeltsin 57 once considered a protege of soviet leader mikhail 
s gorbachev was fired as moscow party chief nov 11 after 
criticizing the slow pace of reform and the partys style of 
leadership at a party meeting 
one week after his ouster yeltsin was named first deputy 
chairman of the state construction committee a government job that 
carries the rank of minister but that is clearly inferior to the 
post of moscow party boss 
stoitelnaya gazeta sought yeltsins comments in connection with 
a frontpage article on woes in the soviet contruction industry 
which is having to conform to the same costcutting and efficiency 
measures as the rest of the economy 
the situation here is serious in effect yeltsin said 
thus cardinal changes in our branch are especially needed 
he said gorbachevs economic and social reform program known as 
perestroika or reconstruction had reached a decisive 
phase 
its success yeltsin added depends on the support of the wide 
masses of workers who hope for changes for the better in their 
lives and link them with perestroika 
yeltsin who graduated as a construction engineer in 1955 from 
the ural polytechnical institute in sverdlovsk said the reform 
program could bring quick beneficial changes in construction 
what is reconstruction in a position to give people in the 
near future i think first of all an improvement in housing 
conditions growth in the number of uptodate medical 
installations schools and kindergartens yelstin said 
housing is an acute problem in the soviet union where one 
family in five lives in dormitories or communal dwellings a party 
program has called for the construction of enough new housing so 
