that there was an awful lot of fried food and salt if everything 
is fried then the food group balance doesnt matter that much 
miss pratt said 
miss pratt recently froze five school lunches and extracted or 
calculated their fats proteins sodium cholesterol and 
carbohydrates using equipment at the oklahoma food laboratory in 
oklahoma city 30 miles west of here 
she did the analysis as a project for the oklahoma science and 
engineering fair her effort was recognized by the oklahoma section 
of the american chemical society as a firstplace project in the 
junior high division 
the meals were high in sodium calories and cholesterol 
miss pratt said they do have a high level of protein as well 
but its unhealthy to go through school eating that kind of diet 
eating habits that are formed in early childhood have been 
found to be extremely resistant to change and seem to affect 
individuals the rest of their lives the teenager said 
state officials said students wouldnt eat more nutritious fare 
when it was offered and often threw the food in the trash 
if the schools are to change well have also have to change 
the likes and dislikes coming into the cafeteria said tom 
freeman assistant superintendant and director of child nutrition 
programs for the state department of education 
the days of liver and spinach are past freeman said 
