a special grand jury today called city 
officials conduct in the 1985 move siege that led to 11 deaths 
totally unacceptable but returned no criminal indictments in 
what it called the citys greatest tragedy 
eleven people died and 61 homes were destroyed on may 13 1985 
when police dropped a bomb on a barricaded west philadelphia row 
house occupied by the radical group move 
applying the law to the facts as we find them no charges are 
warranted yet we do not exonerate the men responsible for this 
disaster the grand jury said in its 279page report rather 
than a vindication of those officials this report should stand as 
a permanent record of their morally reprehensible behavior 
this city its leaders and citizens must never forget the 
terrible cost of their misjudgments 
the confrontation started after neighbors who had been targets 
of threats and harassment for several years told authorities they 
would try to evict move themselves unless the city acted 
the grand jury report released this afternoon denounced the 
citys planning for and actions in the siege as incompetent and 
inept it especially castigated mayor w wilson goode 
as the citys chief executive officer and the man legally 
responsible for law enforcement in the city goode delegated too 
much deferred too often and asked too few questions the report 
said 
the move group championed backtonature rituals lived in filth 
with rats and other animals refused to send their children to 
school and disobeyed health and safety laws it was decimated by 
the disaster and most of its living members are now in jail 
