that any economist dares to stand 
reviewing the more recent analyses from banks brokers 
businesses and academe it becomes clear that the big unknowns 
being discussed today are less economic than political elections 
trade policies wars oil availability 
how could the stock market crash be an economic nonevent 
rather than a forecast of things to come 
for one thing very few families had large holdings of common 
stocks one study for example shows that less than 2 percent of 
households had more than 100000 of direct holdings 
more and more the crash is being viewed in technical rather 
than economic terms as an event that had little significance as an 
omen of things to come but as an internal failure of the market 
mechanism itself 
while it still has an impact on the thinking of many people 
that impact seems to be waning and helping to put it in the past 
are those encouraging economic statistics that suggest continued 
moderate growth 
